-- 2010-12-19T02:33:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-19/arcelormittal-raises-baffinland-offer-to-1-23-a-share-lowers-acceptance.html
The union representing pilots at
Cathay Pacific Airways Ltd., Hong Kong’s biggest carrier,
recommended they accept a management pay offer, the South China
Morning Post reported.  John Findlay, assistant general secretary to the Aircrew
Officers Association and a member of the union’s negotiating
team, said the group advised Cathay’s about 2,500 pilots accept
an offer made by the airline on Friday, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
